Gummy tack must be completely removed and the space should be returned to as good or better condition than when it was found at the end of your rental. While here please enjoy the complimentary tea and hot water located in the Parlor. We ask that guests do not loiter in the Parlor before, during, or after your rental as it is the adjoining room for our other event space and could cause noise interference. We allow topless yoga classes but bottoms must stay on at all times for sanitation. Please notify us if you will be using the space for classes with nudity. There is no drug use or smoking permitted within 25 feet of the building at any time. Violence of any kind including verbal disparaging remarks will result in immediate expulsion. The space is located next to and below residential units and by renting our space it is agreed that the sound will be kept to reasonable levels and if there is any doubt or question about the volume the renter will ask The Center SF staff. Music must end by 11PM Sunday-Thursday and by midnight Friday and Saturday. Guests are asked not to loiter outside in the alley past 8pm to respect our neighbors. We are glad to accommodate the setup of projectors, displays, P/A system, etc. Please let us know in advance if you have any special requests.  Catering and food We encourage you to choose a caterer from our list of preferred caterers. In order to cancel an event a request must be submitted no less than 14 days prior to the scheduled event date. If this time frame for cancellation is not honored a charge 25% of the total negotiated event price will be incurred by the owner of the credit card. Any changes to arrangements made with catering companies are the sole responsibility of the event’s host.  Guest Count Policy A guest count must be confirmed 7 days before your event’s scheduled date. If we do not receive a confirmed guest count 7 days prior to your event, we will use the original estimated guest count. We realize that changes do occur, and we are willing to accommodate a 10% increase in your guest count, granted the space is available. Any increase in guest count will be charged accordingly. We will only accept personal checks as advance payment for your event.  Conduct and Liability reserves us the right to remove any guest in the case of odious conduct. We ask that the host maintains that his/her guests behave responsibly. During the event, the host is responsible for any loss or damages to The space or any of the artworks held within.
